Historicon 2024 Registration | Registration

----- PAYPAL Announcement -----
A number of instances have arisen with the use of PayPal where payments are being taken but there's no corresponding transaction in our system. Until we can resolve this issue we will not be accepting PayPal payments. We're sorry for the inconvenience.

You may purchase ONE paid Full Convention Badge per member account.
One Membership = One Discounted Member Badge

If you wish to register another playing, adult attendee it must be under their own account and, in order to get the Member discount, under their own Membership.

Use the Save & Add another Attendee button for Spouse or Youth (14 and under) Badges.

  • Free Spouse Badges are Non-Playing and are not eligible for Game Selection
  • Spouse and Youth Badges are NOT eligible for Wally's Basement Table Purchases

    • Wally's Basement Tables purchased under a Spouse or Youth badge will be not be honored. Refunds are at the discretion of the Convention Director

If you have any difficulties or questions, please use the Contact Us Form (Upper Right side) to request assistance.

Badge Terms:
The purchase, by any means, of any HMGS Show/Event Badge admits one person to the exhibit halls and other free events. The appropriate ticket is necessary for admittance into some events and areas. Check program book or event desl for details. In accepting this badge and in consideration for being admitted to the show/event indicated on the front of this badge, the holder and his or her ward(s) and/or guardian(s) consent to being photographed (by film, tape, digitally, or any other means) for exhibition in all media. Holder also hereby: (1) releases HMGS from any liability for loss or damage to persons or property, infringement of any right, or any other claim or course of action of any kind; (2) authorizes and permits HMGS and its designees to use his or her name, voice, likeness, and all reproductions thereof, in all media now and hereafter known for all purposes in perpetuity; and (3) agrees to comply with all the rules and regulations of the show/event indicated on the front of this badge. HMGS show/event management reserves the right to deny entry or remove from the show/event facilities [including, but not limited to, the hotel(s), convention center(s), and other similar area(s)] any person who, in HMGS show/event management’s sole and absolute discretion, is behaving or threatening to behave in a manner which HMGS show/event management reasonably considers to be disruptive to the show/event, or which HMGS show/event management reasonably considers will pose a threat to the health or safety of others. Badges are not exchangeable for any reason and are issued to the person named only. Refunds for convention registrations are at the discretion of HMGS, inc. Requests must be received in writing prior to first day of the convention. All trademarks are property of the Historical Miniatures Gaming Society (HMGS). www.hmgs.org.

W18:307 — Dreadnaughts at War FULL 
Presenter: Kim Young
6:00 PM10:00 PM
7/17/2024 6:00 PM - 10:00 PM

W18:307  — Dreadnaughts at War —  GM: Kim Young , Sponsor: NONE, Prize: Copy of game rules, Period: World War I, Scale: 1:6000th, Rules: Fighting Battleships, Description: German Admiral Scheer shows his High Seas Fleet off the coast of Norway in hopes of catching a portion of the British Grand Fleet and defeating it. This is a multi-squadron level game involving over 30 battleships and battle cruisers. Players will each command a squadron of 3 to 5 Dreadnoughts. Ships will move and fight in squadron formation in this game with focus on guns, armor and speed and not minutia and endless detail. If you where a fan of the old Avalon Hill game Jutland and large fleet actions, then you will enjoy this. [Location: Heritage: HR-12]

W19:143 — Chippewa & Lundy's Lane July 1814 FULL 
Presenter: Robert Durst
7:00 PM10:00 PM
7/17/2024 7:00 PM - 10:00 PM

W19:143  — Chippewa & Lundy's Lane July 1814 —  GM: Robert Durst , Sponsor: NONE, Prize: NONE, Period: War of 1812, Scale: 12mm, Rules: Command and Colors, Description: The U.S. Army of the North is determined to wrest control of the Niagara River valley from the British. Winfield Scott's brigade spearheads the advance into Canada. Scott runs head-on into a small force attempting to delay the Americans long enough for the Canadian regulars and militia to set up a defensive line further north at Lundy's Lane. Both battles will be fought. Units that survive Chippewa will reappear at Lundy's Lane alongside other units of the opposing armies. [Location: Heritage: HR-44]

W20:496 — Wars of Oz - Australians in Afghanistan 2011 FULL 
Presenter: Martyn Kelly & WAMP
8:00 PM11:00 PM
7/17/2024 8:00 PM - 11:00 PM

W20:496  — Wars of Oz - Australians in Afghanistan 2011 —  GM: Martyn Kelly & WAMP, Sponsor: NONE, Prize: NONE, Period: Modern, Scale: 28mm, Rules: Force on Force, Description: A four-man "Australian SAS team"  was inserted by helicopter overnight to recon a small village where high value Taliban leaders are meeting.  Unfortunately, a local goat herder wandered close to their position, and they were compromised.  What started out as a routine recon mission has developed into a firefight in which they are outgunned.   A regular Aussie infantry unit in Bushmaster vehicles has been sent to extract the SAS team. This game is ideal for players who are new to the rules.   Hold onto your didgeridoos and boomerangs, this game is going to be a fast way to start your convention.  No food or drink at the table. [Location: Heritage: HR-11]

T09:144 — Battle of Trent's Reach, 25 January 1865 FULL 
Presenter: Robert Durst
9:00 AM12:00 PM
7/18/2024 9:00 AM - 12:00 PM

9:00:00 AM  — Battle of Trent's Reach, 25 January 1865  —  GM: Robert Durst , Sponsor: NONE, Prize: NONE, Period: American Civil War, Scale: 6mm, Rules: Portable Ironclads & Dawn of Iron, Description: Based at Chaffin's Bluff on the James, the James River Squadron had the highest concentration of ironclads in the Confederacy. At the end of December 1864 the Union Navy reassigned some ships to the Ft. Fisher operation in N.C. The rebels saw an opportunity to disrupt the siege of Richmond, by attacking the Union Army's main supply depot at City Point. The Confederate ships start their run in the dark, hoping to navigate the sunken obstacles and minefield, pushing past the shore batteries, before being discovered. The James River Squadron has 3 ironclads and some armed gunboats in support. The Union has a double turret monitor and an armed ferryboat & double ender in support. There are also some reinforcements. [Location: Commonwealth: CW-76]

S19:698 — Test of Honour - Shogun and the Last Samurai — Theme Game FULL 
Presenter: David Hill
7:00 PM10:00 PM
7/20/2024 7:00 PM - 10:00 PM

7:00:00 PM  — Test of Honour - Shogun and the Last Samurai — Theme Game —  GM: David Hill , Sponsor: Things from the Basement, Your Hobby Place Ltd. and the Metropolitan Wargamers., Prize: Vendor Discounts, Period: Samurai, Scale: 28mm, Rules: Test of Honour - Quick Play, Description: For fans of the recent Shogun series and the less recent Last Samurai movie, this is the game for you. Test of Honour is a fun, fast-paced 28mm samurai skirmish game that I have further streamlined after dozens of convention games and hundreds of players. Don't be scared by the high player count, this is really six separate four-player scenarios played at the same time, with alternating activations (i.e. your turn is every other minute, not hour). With new scenarios, terrain and figures from the series and film, honor and glory await! Quick play rules (one piece of paper!) will be taught. Kids welcome with accompanying adult. All miniatures and materials provided, just bring a fun attitude. [Location: Freedom Foyer: FP-1]

T20:848 — Ticket To Ride Rails to Sails (world Map) 
Presenter: Anthony Dewall & Boardgame Library
8:00 PM11:00 PM
7/18/2024 8:00 PM - 11:00 PM

8:00:00 PM  — Ticket To Ride Rails to Sails (world Map)   —   GM: Anthony Dewall & Boardgame Library, Prize: Yes if event is full,  Rules: Standard rules, Description: In Ticket to Ride: Rails & Sails players start with tickets in hand that show two cities, and over the course of the game they try to collect colored cards, then claim routes on the game board with their colored train and ship tokens, scoring points while doing so. When any player has six or fewer tokens in their supply, each player takes two more turns, then the game ends. At that point, if they've created a continuous path between the two cities on a ticket, then they score the points on that ticket; if not, then they lose points instead. By land and by sea, connect valuable cities across the Great Lakes or even the world. 2-5 players about 120-150 min to play [Location: Board Game Area: ]

11:00:00 AM  — Tsuro   —   GM: Anthony Dewall & Boardgame Library, Prize: Yes if event is full, Period: Rules: Standard rules, Description: A beautiful and beautifully simple game of laying a tile before your own token to continue its path on each turn. The goal is to keep your token on the board longer thananyone else's, but as the board fills up this becomes harder because there are fewer empty spaces left... and another player's tile may also extend your own path in a direction you'd rather not go. Easy to introduce to new players. Play tiles and move around the board. Try to outlast your opponents. 2-8 players about 30-60 min play time [Location: Board Game Area: ]

F21:856 — Virulence 
Presenter: Anthony Dewall & Boardgame Library
9:00 PM11:00 PM
7/19/2024 9:00 PM - 11:00 PM

9:00:00 PM  — Virulence   —   GM: Anthony Dewall & Boardgame Library, Prize: Yes if event is full, Rules: Standard rules, Description: Each round, players secretly choose one Virus card from their hand, place it face down on the table, then simultaneously flip these Virus cards to reveal each player's (and thus each virus') virulence. In order from the highest to the lowest virulence, players then take turns selecting from the available Viral Component cards, each awarding points in a variety of ways, or allowing that player to build their hand of Virus Cards allowing them to win critical components later. Players take on the role of viruses competing to infect a host cell in order to replicate their own viral components, thus scoring points. 2-5 Players about 30 min [Location: Board Game Area: ]

1:00:00 PM  — Wings of War: Famous Aces (2004)   —   GM: Anthony Dewall & Boardgame Library, Prize: Yes if event is full, Period: World War I,  Rules: Standard rules, Description: Wings of War: Famous Aces is the first set of the WWI collection. S13:837 — Tsuro 
Presenter: Anthony Dewall & Boardgame Library
1:00 PM3:00 PM
7/20/2024 1:00 PM - 3:00 PM

1:00:00 PM  — Tsuro   —   GM: Anthony Dewall & Boardgame Library,  Prize: Yes if event is full, Rules: Standard rules, Description: A beautiful and beautifully simple game of laying a tile before your own token to continue its path on each turn. The goal is to keep your token on the board longer than anyone else's, but as the board fills up this becomes harder because there are fewer empty spaces left... and another player's tile may also extend your own path in a direction you'd rather not go. Easy to introduce to new players. Play tiles and move around the board. Try to outlast your opponents. 2-8 players about 30-60 min play time [Location: Board Game Area: ]

7:00:00 PM  — Catan (The Settlers of Catan)   —   GM: Anthony Dewall & Boardgame Library, Prize: Yes if event is full, Rules: Standard rules, Description: In CATAN, players try to be the dominant force on the island of Catan by building settlements, cities, and roads. On each turn dice are rolled to determine what resources the island produces. Players build by spending resources (sheep, wheat, wood, brick and ore) that are depicted by these resource cards; each land type, with the exception of the unproductive desert, produces a specific resource: hills produce brick, forests produce wood, mountains produce ore, fields produce wheat, and pastures produce sheep. HU103: Army Painting, Dry Brushing 
Presenter: Todd Pressley
10:00 AM11:30 AM
7/18/2024 10:00 AM - 11:30 AM

Description: Dry brushing is a technique that many people have tried or use only in specific circumstances. A common complaint is that dry brushing results in miniatures which are chalky or dusty. Great if you are painting armored vehicles but terrible on faces. Fear not! This does not have to be so! This class explores techniques that avoid chalkiness and creates miniatures that rival airbrushing, resulting in smooth color transitions. Students will use dry brush pallets and sponges to improve their dry brush experience. These techniques can be used on any size miniature to speed troops onto the battlefield. Young persons are welcome if accompanied by an adult also in the class.

Learning techniques for basic priming all the way up to fine line camouflage. Learn how to keep your airbrush functioning all the time and not failing. Very simple techniques to make you successful every time.

HU141: Back to Base-icks! 
Presenter: Dennis Jensen
10:00 AM11:30 AM
7/20/2024 10:00 AM - 11:30 AM

Description: In this class students will learn a variety of techniques to create bases through a variety of theaters. Jungles, deserts, and winter bases will all be covered. This is a lecture class.

HU142: Color Mixing or Why Your Colors Are Coming Out Wrong 
Presenter: Tanya Brewer
12:00 PM1:30 PM
7/20/2024 12:00 PM - 1:30 PM

Description: So you tried to mix a highlight for your favorite color and it came out all wrong?  Come learn more than basic color theory so you get the color you want more reliably.  This is a class where you're going to want to take notes.

HU143: Gearing Up For Gaslands 
Presenter: Joseph Mcguire
12:00 PM1:30 PM
7/20/2024 12:00 PM - 1:30 PM

Description: We are all kids at heart here.  Come learn how to make an awesome battle car using Matchbox and Hot Wheels cars.  Make the toy you wanted as child as you add weapons and armor and even paint the model to a rusty finish.  All materials will be provided.

HU144: Large Scale Figures 
Presenter: Dorothy Catapano Walker
12:00 PM3:30 PM
7/20/2024 12:00 PM - 3:30 PM

Description: Go big or go home!!!! Well maybe not.  In the world of figure painting, large scale (54 mm and above) is all about the details and subtle color shading and blending. Don’t let the scale intimidate you. Come learn how to create subtle shifts in colors --- from shadow to highlight. We will learn how to bring out those details that make large scale figures so amazing when they are finished. Students will receive one 72mm figure from Reaper. Students should be comfortable with basic painting techniques and have adequate brush control. This Class is two sessions back to back.

HU145: Airbrushing Never Fail, Part Two FULL 
Presenter: Mark Franke
2:00 PM3:30 PM
7/20/2024 2:00 PM - 3:30 PM

Description: You must’ve taken airbrush class one from me or be familiar with airbrushing to some degree.  In this class we will teach some advanced techniques of camouflaging and weathering. Please bring a model that you’re working on; a tank would be preferable.

HU146: Street Trash 
Presenter: Don Goddard
2:00 PM3:30 PM
7/20/2024 2:00 PM - 3:30 PM

Description: Learn some fast and easy techniques for adding litter and detritus to your modern boards using cheap, readily available materials. Great for adding visual interest and obstacles.

HU147: Advanced Beginners 
Presenter: Gregory Zuniga
4:00 PM5:30 PM
7/20/2024 4:00 PM - 5:30 PM

Description: For everyone who has learned the basics and is ready for the next step, this is it. If you've tried drybrushing and inking your models and you'd like to do more, this class will help you move to the next level. Covers layering, glazing, and other techniques to move your skills to the next level.

HU148: Barbed Wire 
Presenter: Tim Peaslee
4:00 PM5:30 PM
7/20/2024 4:00 PM - 5:30 PM

Description: Barbed wire was a constant presence in 20th century warfare. This is a hands on class to show you how to make great looking barbed wire emplacements. This is a hands on class, so come prepared to build something.

HU149: Freehand for the Non-artist 
Presenter: Gregory Zuniga
7:30 PM9:00 PM
7/20/2024 7:30 PM - 9:00 PM

Description: Can you paint a miniature but can't draw? Want to add a little something to your banners, armor plates, and free spaces? Come join Greg and learn how to transfer a design that you are inspired by onto your figures. Lose the fear of what it often considered a very challenging skill in miniature painting.

HU150: Flip This Project 
Presenter: Tim Peaslee, Don Goddard
7:30 PM9:00 PM
7/20/2024 7:30 PM - 9:00 PM

Description: Having trouble with a terrain piece? Bring it in and let the Hobby Univsity staff help with guidance and construction help. Our knowledgeable terrain gurus have years of experience and know which pitfalls to avoid and how to fix them if one didn't. Plenty of seats and materials available, even to finish class projects or repair materials that did not survive the trip to the convention.

T12:981 — Battle of Shanghai 1932 
Presenter: Ching Chin Historical
12:00 PM1:00 PM
7/18/2024 12:00 PM - 1:00 PM

Battle of Shanghai 1932  —  GM: Ching Chin Historical, Period: Inter-War, Scale: , Description: The Battle of Shanghai in 1932 was a pivotal battle in China which could have saved Asia from World War II.  A contest between the newly re-united Nationalist China and the aggressive Japanese Empire, the battle is a forgotten turning point in the origins of World War II, pitting Japan's well-equipped Army and Navy against China's stubborn provincial forces and crack Central Government troops. This talk is a companion to the game session replaying the battle on an operational level.  The talk will not only cover operational history but will include insights on World War II., [Location: Montgomery House: ]
T13:964 — Wargaming Alternative Military Technologies at Gettysburg --Theme 
Presenter: Sean Barnett Gaming
1:00 PM2:00 PM
7/18/2024 1:00 PM - 2:00 PM

Wargaming Alternative Military Technologies at Gettysburg --Theme —  GM: Sean Barnett Gaming, Period: American Civil War, Description: A discussion of how the RAND Corporation designed two wargames of the Battle of Gettysburg for the U.S. Army in which the armies could employ military technologies that were available in 1863 but which were not used in the actual battle. The games allowed Army officers and staff to experiment with alternative technologies in a historical setting and think about how technologies are developed into military capabilities and how they can influence the best way for an army to fight.  [Location: Montgomery House: ]

T14:961 — Festung 44 - The Fuehrers Fortress Folly 
Presenter: Jeff Schultz Historical
2:00 PM3:00 PM
7/18/2024 2:00 PM - 3:00 PM

Festung 44 - The Fuehrers Fortress Folly  —  GM: Jeff Schultz Historical, Period: World War II, Description: Join us for a brief discussion of select Wehrmacht fortresses of 1944 (80th anniversary edition), ranging from aspects of the Atlantic Wall to the Ostfront with particular focus on the Channel Islands and the Wellenbrecher (wave-breaker) concept implications for the Soviet 1944 offensives. As the war progressed, Berlins fortunes grew increasingly grimmer amid the inexorable Soviet advance, and the opening of the Second Front in France made short work of years of construction and defensive efforts, all of which contributed to the 1945 collapse.  [Location: Montgomery House: ]

T15:974 — Operation COBRA from the ground up: George Wilson's experience in Operation COBRA, 25 July-2 August 1944 
Presenter: John Stapleton Historical
3:00 PM4:00 PM
7/18/2024 3:00 PM - 4:00 PM

Operation COBRA from the ground up: George Wilson's experience in Operation COBRA, 25 July-2 August 1944  —  GM: John Stapleton Historical, Period: World War II, Description: George Wilson was an infantry platoon leader in E Company, 2nd battalion, 22nd Infantry Regiment, 4th Infantry Division.  In this presentation, I explore how the 22nd Infantry Regiment together with the 66th Armored Regiment which comprised Combat Command A  prepared for Operation COBRA, executed the attack, and experienced the St. Lo breakthrough during the last week of July 1944.  Learn how the US Army learned to overcome both the Normandy hedgerows and the vaunted Wehrmacht.  [Location: Montgomery House: ]

T16:973 — LT. George Wilson's War, 1944-1945 
Presenter: Steve Waddell Historical
4:00 PM5:00 PM
7/18/2024 4:00 PM - 5:00 PM

LT. George Wilson's War, 1944-1945  —  GM: Steve Waddell Historical, Period: World War II, Description: One of the best, if not the best, World War II memoir is: If You Survive: From Normandy to the Battle of the Bulge to the End of World War II, One American Officers Riveting True Story.  Join me for an examination of LT Wilsons wartime experience and the many leadership lessons he shares with his readers. Learn the rest of the story as I share what I learned speaking with CPT George Wilson back in 1998. Location: Montgomery House: ]

T17:979 — "D-DAY DISASTER" 
Presenter: Peter Panzeri Historical
5:00 PM6:00 PM
7/18/2024 5:00 PM - 6:00 PM

"D-DAY DISASTER"  —  GM: Peter Panzeri Historical, Sponsor: THE DUKE SEIFRIED FOUNDATION, Period: World War II, Description: Join "KILLING BIN LADEN" author Pete Panzeri for a thought-provoking presentation on "Real & Potential Cataclysmic Disasters" of OPERATION OVERLORD: undeniably one of the most pivotal and decisive battles in all of military history, but also one "rife with disaster" both actual & potential. As a decorated veteran of "The Largest Tank Battle in History," Panzeri will apply key details for a no-nonsense approach on how D-Day succeeded despite so many disasters.  And "How it is arguably, the most significant/irrevocable battle in of all of military history." ONE-TIME ONLY at Hcon'24  [Location: Montgomery House: ]

As claimants vie for de jure authority under the titulature of Byzantium, de facto legitimacy is expressed through military victory. As the Byzantines struggle to win independence, join this lecture to learn about the role of the Byzantine Emperor as a Christian warrior, the function and layout of his soldiers, the types of equipment, foreign auxiliaries of these tumultuous tines and more!  [Location: Montgomery House: ]

While famous for their two wars with the Romans, the Dacians were much more than barbarians on the border of the Empire. F17:980 — ROSEBUD to LITTLE-BIGHORN: INSEPARABLE DISASTERS 
Presenter: Peter Panzeri Historical

ROSEBUD to LITTLE-BIGHORN: INSEPARABLE DISASTERS  —  GM: Peter Panzeri Historical, Sponsor: THE DUKE SEIFRIED FOUNDATION, Period: 19th Century, Description: Join "LITTLE BIGHORN 1876" author Pete Panzeri for an in-depth exposition on the two most inseparable and cataclysmic defeats of ALL of the Western American-Indian Wars. As a decorated leader and combat veteran, Panzeri will apply as many "not-so-well-known" details as time permits, and a no-nonsense approach to convey a "soldiers-eye-view" of the obvious-yet-ignored keys to this campaign. And "Why is one a "disaster" and the other a "setback?"   Just how did all of this happen? Who did well? Who did badly? Who paid the price? Who was blamed? Who was not blamed? And Why.  [Location: Montgomery House: ]

S13:962 — Three Raiders, Three Wars: Commerce Raiders as Effective Maritime Guerrillas, 1862-1943 
Presenter: Jeff Schultz Historical
1:00 PM2:00 PM
7/20/2024 1:00 PM - 2:00 PM

Three Raiders, Three Wars: Commerce Raiders as Effective Maritime Guerrillas, 1862-1943  —  GM: Jeff Schultz Historical, Sponsor: NONE, Prize: NONE, Period: Various, Description: Join us to learn more about select commerce raiders across three major conflicts: the American Civil War, World War I and World War II. We will focus on three belligerents: the Confederacy, Imperial Germany and Nazi Germany efforts to wage maritime guerilla warfare against the large merchant fleets of their foes; featuring the most successful raiders, the tactics used and other related information. Collectively, this lecture hopes to offer insights as to how commerce raiding represented a relatively cost-effective means to disrupt the enemy until effective countermeasures arose.  [Location: Montgomery House: ]

S16:963 — Sea Soldiers, Sailors, and Schutztruppen: German Troop Types and Tactics in the Herero War 
Presenter: Roy Jones Historical
4:00 PM5:00 PM
7/20/2024 4:00 PM - 5:00 PM

Sea Soldiers, Sailors, and Schutztruppen: German Troop Types and Tactics in the Herero War  —  GM: Roy Jones Historical, Period: Colonial, Description: The aggressiveness of the Herero's pressing after the Germans broke on the resistance of the German Marines. German official history, 1904. Imperial Marines (Seesoldaten, or Sea Soldiers) survived against overwhelming odds through their exceptional tenacity and maneuverability. Sailors had extraordinary morale, triumphantly charging uphill against Herero's in superior positions. Schutztruppen were masters of the bayonet, forcing Herero's to abandon their trenches. This talk focuses on these forces. [Location: Montgomery House: ]

F09:608 — Out of Ammunition: God Save the King — Theme Game FULL

9:00:00 AM  — Out of Ammunition: God Save the King — Theme Game —  GM: John Emmett & LARD America, Sponsor: NONE, Prize: NONE, Period: World War II, Scale: 28mm, Rules: Chain of Command, Description: Arnhem, Netherlands, 1944: Although successful in repelling the early German probing attacks, John Frost's perimeter around the Arnhem road bridge's north end continued to shrink. F15:590 — Poorly clothed, worse fed, and seldom paid - The Mexican War with Sharp Practice FULL 
Presenter: Michael Ovsenik & LARD America
3:00 PM7:00 PM
7/19/2024 3:00 PM - 7:00 PM

3:00:00 PM  — Poorly clothed, worse fed, and seldom paid - The Mexican War with Sharp Practice   —   GM: Michael Ovsenik & LARD America, Sponsor: Goonhammer, Prize: NONE, Period: Mexican War, Scale: 28mm, Rules: Sharp Practice, Description: Often overlooked as just an education for Civil War officers, the Mexican - American War is a very interesting conflict to research and game. The Mexican army had soldiers who were devoted but ill led and poorly equipped. American regulars were well equipped and trained and able to take on forces many times their own size. This game will use Sharp Practice to showcase a small engagement in Mexico between US  regulars and Mexican forces. Have a great time playing the period!  [Location: Heritage: HR-27]
